<li id="cite_note-Friedman_page233-31"><span class="mw-cite-backlink noprint"><a href="#cite_ref-Friedman_page233_31-0">↑</a> </span><span class="reference-text">Page 233 <span class="ouvrage" id="FriedmanRose_Friedman1998"><span class="ouvrage" id="Milton_FriedmanRose_Friedman1998"><abbr class="abbr indicateur-langue" title="Langue : anglais">(en)</abbr> Milton <span class="nom_auteur">Friedman</span> et <a href="/wiki/Rose_Friedman" title="Rose Friedman"><span class="nom_auteur">Rose Friedman</span></a>, <cite class="italique" lang="en">Two lucky people&#160;: memoirs</cite>, Chicago, The University of Chicago Press, <time>1998</time> <small style="line-height:1em;">(<a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Sp%C3%A9cial:Ouvrages_de_r%C3%A9f%C3%A9rence/0226264149" title="Spécial:Ouvrages de référence/0226264149"><span class="nowrap">0226264149</span></a>)</small><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Two+lucky+people+%3A+memoirs&amp;rft.place=Chicago&amp;rft.pub=The+University+of+Chicago+Press&amp;rft.aulast=Friedman&amp;rft.aufirst=Milton&amp;rft.au=Rose+Friedman&amp;rft.date=1998&amp;rft.isbn=0226264149&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Ffr.wikipedia.org%3AFriedrich+Hayek"></span></span></span>.</span>
